chatgpt_solution: We have  \[(\sqrt[3]{13})^6 = \left[(13)^{1/3}\right]^6 = (13)^{(1/3)(6)} = (13)^2=\boxed{169}.\]We can also find this result by noting that $\sqrt[3]{13}=\sqrt[3]{13^1}$, so $\left(\sqrt[3]{13}\right)^6=\left(\sqrt[3]{13^1}\right)^6=\sqrt[3]{13^{1\cdot 6}}=\sqrt[3]{13^6}=13^{\frac63}=13^2$.
